# Litmus — optional model key.
#
# Without a key, Litmus runs fully: deterministic statistical forensics,
# OpenAlex retrieval, calibration, grounding. It uses a transparent
# deterministic adjudicator and a heuristic claim extractor.
#
# With a key, three steps upgrade automatically:
#   • claim extraction         → claude-sonnet-5 (multi-claim, evidence-linked)
#   • adjudication             → claude-opus-4-8 (extended thinking)
#   • literature stance        → claude-haiku-4-5 (supports/contradicts/failed)
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` and restart the dev/prod server.

ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# ---- optional tuning (generous defaults; raise/lower for accuracy vs. cost) ----
# Ensemble: adjudicate each claim with several Claude models and aggregate the
# scores (more robust, more verifiable). Default is a single model.
# LITMUS_ENSEMBLE_MODELS=claude-opus-4-8,claude-sonnet-5
#
# Max central claims adjudicated per paper (each is one model call, run in parallel):
# LITMUS_MAX_CLAIMS=12
# LITMUS_ADJ_CONCURRENCY=6
#
# Output token caps per step (a ceiling, not a target):
# LITMUS_TOK_EXTRACT=16000
# LITMUS_TOK_ADJUDICATE=16000
# LITMUS_TOK_STANCE=12000
# LITMUS_TOK_VERIFY=12000
# LITMUS_TOK_PDF=16000
# LITMUS_TOK_NARRATIVE=3000    # grounded executive summary of the audit
#
# Retrieval: works fetched per source before merge/dedup. Queried in parallel:
# OpenAlex, Crossref, Semantic Scholar, Europe PMC, PubMed, arXiv, DOAJ,
# DataCite, OpenAIRE, plus a citation graph (OpenAlex + OpenCitations + Semantic
# Scholar) and DOI-level transparency signals (Unpaywall open-access, bioRxiv/
# medRxiv preprint, ClinicalTrials.gov registrations, Crossref funders).
# LITMUS_RETRIEVE=20
#
# CORE (core.ac.uk) — 300M+ open-access papers. Free key adds it as a source;
# without a key CORE is simply skipped. Register at https://core.ac.uk/services/api
# CORE_API_KEY=
#
# Chars of paper text sent to claim extraction:
# LITMUS_IN_PAPER=400000
